### ── DELIVERY SERVICE (/deliveries) ────────────────────────────────────────
### Environment: Ctrl+Shift+P → Rest Client: Switch Environment → dev
### Prerequisite: get orderId from sales.http → createOrder; payment must be completed.

### 1. Schedule delivery — Manager
### orderId: replace with ID returned from createOrder in sales.http
# @name scheduleDelivery
POST {{baseUrl}}/deliveries/scheduleDelivery
Authorization: {{managerAuth}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "orderId": "REPLACE_WITH_ORDER_ID",
  "plannedDate": "2026-07-15"
}

### 2. List deliveries — Admin
GET {{baseUrl}}/deliveries/Deliveries
Authorization: {{adminAuth}}

### 3. List deliveries — Customer Bauer (own order deliveries only)
GET {{baseUrl}}/deliveries/Deliveries
Authorization: {{customerBauerAuth}}

### 4. Update delivery — change date and status
### deliveryId: replace with ID returned from step 1
POST {{baseUrl}}/deliveries/updateDelivery
Authorization: {{managerAuth}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "deliveryId": "REPLACE_WITH_DELIVERY_ID",
  "plannedDate": "2026-07-16",
  "status": "IN_PROGRESS"
}

### 5. Complete delivery — DELIVERED
POST {{baseUrl}}/deliveries/completeDelivery
Authorization: {{managerAuth}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "deliveryId": "REPLACE_WITH_DELIVERY_ID"
}

### 6. Schedule delivery as Customer — should be rejected (Manager/Admin only)
POST {{baseUrl}}/deliveries/scheduleDelivery
Authorization: {{customerBauerAuth}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "orderId": "REPLACE_WITH_ORDER_ID",
  "plannedDate": "2026-07-20"
}
